Professor Jay Berzofsky of the U.S. National Cancer Institute in Bethesda, Maryland, said: “Our results indicate that we have a very promising vaccine.”
According to Professor Berzofsky, the protein HER2 “induces an increase in several types of cancer”, including breast, ovarian, lung and colorectal cancer.
A similar approach, taking immune cells to “learn” how to target cancer cells, has proven itself as part of the treatment of one type of leukemia.
